{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1063,"text":"It was April 8, 2003."},{"time":5856,"text":"I was in Baghdad,\ncovering the war in Iraq."},{"time":10405,"text":"That day, Americans tanks\nstarted arriving in Baghdad."},{"time":16039,"text":"We were just a few journalists\nin the Palestine Hotel,"},{"time":23435,"text":"and, as happens in war,"},{"time":25882,"text":"the fighting began to approach\noutside our windows."},{"time":30327,"text":"Baghdad was covered\nin black smoke and oil."},{"time":34955,"text":"It smelled awful."},{"time":36137,"text":"We couldn't see a thing,\nbut we knew what was happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38852,"text":"Of course, I was supposed\nto be writing an article,"},{"time":41366,"text":"but that's how it always goes --"},{"time":42926,"text":"you're supposed to be writing\nand something big happens."},{"time":45588,"text":"So I was in my room on the 16th floor,"},{"time":48339,"text":"writing and looking out the window\nevery now and then"},{"time":51245,"text":"to see what was happening."},{"time":53053,"text":"Suddenly, there was a huge explosion."},{"time":55547,"text":"During the previous three weeks,"},{"time":57507,"text":"there had been shelling\nwith half-ton missiles,"},{"time":61650,"text":"but this time, the shock --"},{"time":64728,"text":"I felt it inside of me,"},{"time":67249,"text":"and I thought, \"It's very close."},{"time":69274,"text":"It's very, very close.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":71296,"text":"So I went down to see what was happening."},{"time":73700,"text":"I went down to the 15th floor"},{"time":77671,"text":"to take a look."},{"time":79043,"text":"And I saw people, journalists,\nscreaming in the hallways."},{"time":82670,"text":"I walked into a room"},{"time":84925,"text":"and realized that it had\nbeen hit by a missile."},{"time":90169,"text":"Someone had been wounded."},{"time":93304,"text":"There was a man near the window,"},{"time":95396,"text":"a cameraman named Taras Protsyuk,"},{"time":100245,"text":"lying face-down."},{"time":106796,"text":"Having worked in a hospital before,\nI wanted to help out."},{"time":110996,"text":"So I turned him over."},{"time":112521,"text":"And when I turned him over,"},{"time":116334,"text":"I noticed that he was open\nfrom sternum to pubis,"},{"time":119509,"text":"but I couldn't see anything,\nnothing at all."},{"time":122467,"text":"All I saw was a white, pearly,\nshiny spot that blinded me,"},{"time":129245,"text":"and I didn't understand what was going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131879,"text":"Once the spot disappeared\nand I could see his wound,"},{"time":134555,"text":"which was very serious,"},{"time":136156,"text":"my buddies and I put a sheet\nunderneath him,"},{"time":138275,"text":"and we carried him onto an elevator\nthat stopped at each of the 15 floors."},{"time":142616,"text":"We put him in a car\nthat took him to the hospital."},{"time":144984,"text":"He died on the way to the hospital."},{"time":146770,"text":"The Spanish cameraman Jos√© Couso,\nwho was on the 14th floor and also hit --"},{"time":151784,"text":"because the shell had exploded\nbetween the two floors --"},{"time":155118,"text":"died on the operating table."},{"time":157078,"text":"As soon as the car left, I went back."},{"time":159499,"text":"There was that article\nI was supposed to write --"},{"time":161856,"text":"which I had to write."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164117,"text":"And so --"},{"time":165870,"text":"I returned to the hotel lobby\nwith my arms covered in blood,"},{"time":172792,"text":"when one of the hotel gofers stopped me"},{"time":175356,"text":"and asked me to pay the tax\nI hadn't paid for 10 days."},{"time":179227,"text":"I told him to get lost."},{"time":181059,"text":"And I said to myself:\n\"Clear your head, put it all aside."},{"time":187097,"text":"If you want to write,\nyou need to put it all aside.\""},{"time":189570,"text":"And that's what I did."},{"time":190809,"text":"I went upstairs, wrote\nmy article and sent it off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195077,"text":"Later, aside from the feeling\nof having lost my colleagues,"},{"time":199895,"text":"something else was bothering me."},{"time":202442,"text":"I kept seeing that shiny, pearly spot,"},{"time":208735,"text":"and I couldn't understand what it meant."},{"time":211731,"text":"And then, the war was over."}]},{"cues":[{"time":216572,"text":"Later, I thought: \"That's not possible.\nI can't just not know what happened.\""},{"time":222692,"text":"Because it wasn't the first time,\nand it didn't only happen to me."},{"time":226177,"text":"I have seen things like that\nhappen to others"},{"time":230106,"text":"in my 20 to 35 years of reporting."},{"time":232798,"text":"I have seen things\nthat had an effect on me too."},{"time":236108,"text":"For example, there was this man\nI knew in Lebanon,"},{"time":239177,"text":"a 25-year-old veteran\nwho had been fighting for five years --"},{"time":242107,"text":"a real veteran -- who we would\nfollow everywhere."},{"time":244474,"text":"He would crawl in the dark\nwith confidence --"},{"time":248731,"text":"he was a great soldier, a true soldier --"},{"time":251167,"text":"so we would follow him,\nknowing that we would be safe with him."},{"time":254548,"text":"And one day, as I was told --"},{"time":256880,"text":"and I've seen him again since --"},{"time":258500,"text":"he was back in the camp, playing cards,"},{"time":260865,"text":"when someone came in next door,"},{"time":264158,"text":"and discharged their weapon."},{"time":266318,"text":"As the gun went off,"},{"time":267850,"text":"that blast, that one shot,\nmade him duck quickly under the table,"},{"time":274204,"text":"like a child."},{"time":275442,"text":"He was shaking, panicking."},{"time":277357,"text":"And since then, he has never\nbeen able to get up and fight."},{"time":282189,"text":"He ended up working as a croupier"},{"time":284905,"text":"in a Beirut casino\nwhere I later found him,"},{"time":287051,"text":"because he couldn't sleep,\nso it was quite a suitable job."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290378,"text":"So I thought to myself,"},{"time":292957,"text":"\"What is this thing that can kill you"},{"time":296035,"text":"without leaving\nany visible scars?"},{"time":300974,"text":"How does that happen?"},{"time":304040,"text":"What is this unknown thing?\""},{"time":307206,"text":"It was too common to be coincidental."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311597,"text":"So I started to investigate --"},{"time":313279,"text":"that's all I know how to do."},{"time":315297,"text":"I started to investigate"},{"time":317164,"text":"by looking through books,"},{"time":320836,"text":"reaching out to psychiatrists,"},{"time":323202,"text":"going to museums, libraries, etc."},{"time":326224,"text":"Finally, I discovered\nthat some people knew about this --"},{"time":330950,"text":"often military psychiatrists --"},{"time":332904,"text":"and that what we were dealing with\nwas called trauma."},{"time":337817,"text":"Americans call it PTSD\nor traumatic neurosis."},{"time":342667,"text":"It was something"},{"time":346262,"text":"that existed,"},{"time":348206,"text":"but that we never spoke about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352206,"text":"So, this trauma --"},{"time":354452,"text":"what is it?"},{"time":355633,"text":"Well, it's an encounter with death."},{"time":359126,"text":"I don't know if you've ever had\nan experience with death --"},{"time":361952,"text":"I'm not talking about dead bodies,"},{"time":363859,"text":"or someone's grandfather\nlying in a hospital bed,"},{"time":367484,"text":"or someone who got hit by a car."},{"time":372134,"text":"I'm talking about facing\nthe void of death."},{"time":377688,"text":"And that is something\nno one is supposed to see."},{"time":383885,"text":"People used to say,"},{"time":385751,"text":"\"Neither the sun, nor death\ncan be looked at with a steady eye.\""},{"time":389750,"text":"A human being should not\nhave to face the void of death."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394008,"text":"But when that happens,"},{"time":397801,"text":"it can remain invisible for a while --"},{"time":401573,"text":"days, weeks, months, sometimes years."},{"time":404365,"text":"And then, at some point,"},{"time":407587,"text":"it explodes,"},{"time":408897,"text":"because it's something\nthat has entered your brain --"},{"time":412665,"text":"a sort of window between an image\nand your mind --"},{"time":417340,"text":"that has penetrated your brain,"},{"time":419689,"text":"staying there and taking up\nall the space inside."},{"time":425541,"text":"And there are people --\nmen, women,"},{"time":428858,"text":"who suddenly no longer sleep."},{"time":432376,"text":"And they experience\nhorrible anxiety attacks --"},{"time":434745,"text":"panic attacks, not just minor fears."},{"time":437799,"text":"They suddenly don't want to sleep,"},{"time":440129,"text":"because when they do, they have\nthe same nightmare every night."},{"time":444687,"text":"They see the same image every night."},{"time":446631,"text":"What type of image?"},{"time":448282,"text":"For example, a soldier\nwho enters a building"},{"time":451109,"text":"and comes face to face\nwith another soldier aiming at him."},{"time":453967,"text":"He looks at the gun,\nstraight down the barrel."},{"time":456554,"text":"And this barrel suddenly\nbecomes enormous, deformed."},{"time":460162,"text":"It becomes fluffy, swallowing everything."},{"time":462940,"text":"And he says --"},{"time":466376,"text":"later he will say, \"I saw death."},{"time":468742,"text":"I saw myself dead, therefore I'm dead.\""},{"time":471267,"text":"And from then on, he knows he is dead."},{"time":475148,"text":"It is not a perception --\nhe is convinced that he is dead."},{"time":480057,"text":"In reality, someone came in,\nthe guy left or didn't shoot, whatever,"},{"time":483613,"text":"and he didn't actually get shot --"},{"time":485284,"text":"but to him, he died in that moment."},{"time":487016,"text":"Or it can be the smell\nof a mass grave --"},{"time":489147,"text":"I saw a lot of that in Rwanda."},{"time":491510,"text":"It can be the voice of a friend calling,"},{"time":495113,"text":"and they're being slaughtered\nand there's nothing you can do."},{"time":498897,"text":"You hear that voice,"},{"time":500127,"text":"and you wake up every night --\nfor weeks, months --"},{"time":505657,"text":"in a trance-like state,\nanxious and terrified,"},{"time":508438,"text":"like a child."},{"time":509817,"text":"I have seen men cry --"},{"time":512652,"text":"just like children --"},{"time":514442,"text":"from seeing the same image."}]},{"cues":[{"time":516162,"text":"So having that image\nof horror in your brain,"},{"time":522659,"text":"seeing the void of death --"},{"time":524521,"text":"that analogue of horror\nwhich is hiding something --"},{"time":528250,"text":"will completely take over."},{"time":529528,"text":"You cannot do anything, anything at all."},{"time":531859,"text":"You cannot work anymore,"},{"time":533177,"text":"you cannot love anymore."},{"time":534484,"text":"You go home and don't recognize anyone."},{"time":536435,"text":"You don't even recognize yourself."},{"time":541181,"text":"You hide and don't leave the house,\nyou lock yourself in, you become ill."},{"time":544729,"text":"I know people who placed small cans\noutside their house with coins inside,"},{"time":549167,"text":"in case someone tried to get in."},{"time":551057,"text":"All of a sudden, you feel\nlike you want to die or kill"},{"time":553953,"text":"or hide or run away."},{"time":555525,"text":"You want to be loved,\nbut you hate everyone."},{"time":557700,"text":"It's a feeling that seizes you entirely"},{"time":562644,"text":"day in and day out,"},{"time":564399,"text":"and you suffer tremendously."},{"time":569351,"text":"And no one understands."},{"time":570852,"text":"They say, \"There's nothing wrong with you.\nYou seem fine, you have no injuries."},{"time":574644,"text":"You went to war, came back; you're fine.\""},{"time":578231,"text":"These people suffer tremendously."},{"time":580137,"text":"Some commit suicide."},{"time":582035,"text":"After all, suicide is like updating\nyour daily planner --"},{"time":584773,"text":"I'm already dead,\nI might as well commit suicide."},{"time":587108,"text":"Plus, there is no more pain."},{"time":589067,"text":"Some commit suicide,\nothers end up under the bridge, drinking."},{"time":593121,"text":"Everyone remembers\nthat grandfather or uncle or neighbor"},{"time":597517,"text":"who used to drink, never said a word,"},{"time":599511,"text":"always in a bad mood, beat his wife"},{"time":601304,"text":"and who would end up either sinking\ninto alcoholism or dying."}]},{"cues":[{"time":605457,"text":"And why do we not talk about this?"},{"time":608261,"text":"We don't talk about it because it's taboo."},{"time":612157,"text":"It's not like we don't have the words\nto express the void of death."},{"time":615948,"text":"But others don't want hear it."},{"time":617740,"text":"The first time I returned\nfrom an assignment,"},{"time":619878,"text":"They said, \"Oh! He's back.\""},{"time":621428,"text":"There was a fancy dinner --\nwhite tablecloth, candles, guests."},{"time":624548,"text":"\"Tell us everything!\""},{"time":625764,"text":"Which I did."},{"time":628075,"text":"After 20 minutes, people\nwere giving me dirty looks,"},{"time":630583,"text":"the hostess had her nose in the ashtray."},{"time":632612,"text":"It was horrible and I realized\nI ruined the whole evening."},{"time":635607,"text":"So I don't talk about it anymore."},{"time":637540,"text":"We're just not ready to listen."},{"time":639105,"text":"People say outright: \"Please, stop.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":640857,"text":"Is that a rare occurrence?"},{"time":642978,"text":"No, it's extremely common."},{"time":645404,"text":"One third of the soldiers\nwho died in Iraq --"},{"time":647581,"text":"well, not \"died,\" let me re-phrase that --"},{"time":650127,"text":"one third of the US soldiers\nwho went to Iraq"},{"time":653291,"text":"suffer from PTSD."},{"time":654953,"text":"In 1939, there were still 200,000 soldiers\nfrom the First World War"},{"time":660898,"text":"that were being treated\nin British psychiatric hospitals."},{"time":665066,"text":"In Vietnam, 54,000 people died --"},{"time":667524,"text":"Americans."},{"time":668891,"text":"In 1987, the US government\nidentified 102,000 --"},{"time":673088,"text":"twice as many --"},{"time":674326,"text":"102,000 veterans who died\nfrom committing suicide."},{"time":676974,"text":"Twice as many deaths by suicide\nthan by combat in Vietnam."},{"time":679814,"text":"So you see, this relates to everything,"},{"time":682996,"text":"not just modern warfare,\nbut also ancient wars --"},{"time":685359,"text":"you can read about it,\nthe evidence is there."},{"time":688382,"text":"So why do we not talk about it?"},{"time":690651,"text":"Why have we not talked about it?"},{"time":693120,"text":"The problem is that\nif you don't talk about it,"},{"time":698642,"text":"you're heading for disaster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701528,"text":"The only way to heal --"},{"time":704367,"text":"and the good news here\nis that this is treatable --"},{"time":708829,"text":"think Munch's The Scream, Goya, etc. --"},{"time":710924,"text":"it's indeed treatable."},{"time":712233,"text":"The only way to heal from this trauma,"},{"time":716817,"text":"from this encounter with death\nthat overwhelms, petrifies and kills you"},{"time":721897,"text":"is to find a way to express it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":726540,"text":"People used to say,"},{"time":728303,"text":"\"Language is the only thing\nthat holds all of us together.\""},{"time":731894,"text":"Without language, we're nothing."},{"time":734259,"text":"It's the thing that makes us human."},{"time":736900,"text":"In the face of such a horrible image --"},{"time":738901,"text":"a wordless image of oblivion\nthat obsesses us --"},{"time":744451,"text":"the only way to cope with it"},{"time":748109,"text":"is to put human words to it."},{"time":750234,"text":"Because these people\nfeel excluded from humanity."},{"time":752684,"text":"No one wants to see them anymore\nand they don't want to see anyone."},{"time":755914,"text":"They feel dirty, defiled, ashamed."},{"time":758359,"text":"Someone said, \"Doctor,\nI don't use the subway anymore"},{"time":761627,"text":"because I'm afraid people\nwill see the horror in my eyes.\""},{"time":764865,"text":"Another guy thought he had\na terrible skin disease"},{"time":767755,"text":"and spent six months with dermatologists,\ngoing from doctor to doctor."},{"time":771616,"text":"And then one day, they sent him\nto a psychiatrist."},{"time":774179,"text":"During his second session,\nhe told the psychiatrist"},{"time":776608,"text":"he had a terrible skin disease\nfrom head to toe."},{"time":778962,"text":"The psychiatrist asked,\n\"Why are you in this state?\""},{"time":781905,"text":"And the man said, \"Well, because\nI'm dead, so I must be rotting away.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":785255,"text":"So you see this is something\nthat has a profound effect on people."},{"time":789692,"text":"In order to heal,\nwe need to talk about it."},{"time":792125,"text":"The horror needs to be put into words --"},{"time":796093,"text":"human words, so we can organize it\nand talk about it again."},{"time":800300,"text":"We have to look death in the face."},{"time":805061,"text":"And if we can do that,\nif we can talk about these things,"},{"time":810180,"text":"then step by step,\nby working it out verbally,"},{"time":813629,"text":"we can reclaim our place in humanity."},{"time":817549,"text":"And it is important."},{"time":818837,"text":"Silence kills us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821789,"text":"So what does this mean?"},{"time":823235,"text":"It means that after a trauma,"},{"time":825275,"text":"without question, we lose\nour \"unbearable lightness of being,\""},{"time":828934,"text":"that sense of immortality\nthat keeps us here --"},{"time":831712,"text":"meaning, if we're here, we almost feel\nlike we're immortal, which we're not,"},{"time":835648,"text":"but if we didn't believe that,\nwe'd say, \"What's the point of it all?\""},{"time":839015,"text":"But trauma survivors have lost\nthat feeling of immortality."},{"time":841829,"text":"They've lost their lightness."},{"time":843248,"text":"But they have found something else."},{"time":845011,"text":"So this means that if we manage\nto look death in the face,"},{"time":849546,"text":"and actually confront it,\nrather than keep quiet and hide,"},{"time":854472,"text":"like some of the men or women I know did,"},{"time":856975,"text":"such as Michael from Rwanda,\nCarole from Iraq, Philippe from the Congo"},{"time":863653,"text":"and other people I know,"},{"time":864903,"text":"like Sorj Chalandon, now a great writer,"},{"time":867025,"text":"who gave up field assignments\nafter a trauma."},{"time":869340,"text":"Five friends of mine committed suicide,"},{"time":871582,"text":"they're the ones\nwho did not survive the trauma."}]},{"cues":[{"time":874182,"text":"So if we can look death in the face,"},{"time":879752,"text":"if we, mortal humans, human mortals,"},{"time":882554,"text":"understand that we are human\nand mortal, mortal and human,"},{"time":885419,"text":"if we can confront death\nand identify it once again"},{"time":891690,"text":"as the most mysterious place\nof all mysterious places,"},{"time":895570,"text":"since no one has ever seen it --"},{"time":898150,"text":"if we can give it back this meaning,"},{"time":900837,"text":"yes, we may die,"},{"time":905686,"text":"survive"},{"time":908011,"text":"and come back to life,"},{"time":909462,"text":"but we'll come back stronger than before."},{"time":912579,"text":"Much stronger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":913913,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":915091,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}